    Sample IFIXMessage implementation using FIXMessageWithPluggableStore and an underlying TagValuesAsIndexedByteArray instance for storage.

    This IFIXMessage is most efficient when the incoming data is a byte array in standard FIX format. Its advantage is that it works directly on that byte array without needing to create other objects. (Note that FAST messages do not come in in that form, however). This message type is best suited as a general purpose implementation replacing the legacy Message class.
